ons ({\textless}span class="inline-formula"{\textgreater}\textit{P}{\textless}/span{\textgreater} vs. clear-sky DLR). Such a simple linear sensitivity model was able to reproduce observed {\textless}span class="inline-formula"{\textgreater}\textit{P}{\textless}/span{\textgreater} anomaly time series with similar accuracy to an (uncoupled) atmospheric model (ERA-20CM) and two climate reanalysis (ERA-20C and 20CR). The linear sensitivity breaks down at sub-yearly timescales, whereby the underlying correlations become negligible. Finally, the relevance of the multi-scale framework and its potential for stochastic downscaling applications are demonstrated by deriving accurate monthly {\textless}span class="inline-formula"{\textgreater}\textit{P}{\textless}/span{\textgreater} probability density functions (PDFs) from the reconstructed 2-year {\textless}span class="inline-formula"{\textgreater}\textit{P}{\textless}/span{\textgreater} time series based on scale-invariant arguments alone. The derived monthly PDFs outperform the statistics simulated by ERA-20C, 20CR, and ERA-20CM in reproducing observations.{\textless}/p{\textgreater}},
